cs.CV, cs.GR, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.DB 

The paper deals with correcting annotations of rural buildings in OpenStreetMap using convolutional neural networks. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also involves geographic information systems and remote sensing, which suggests that it could belong to cs.GR (Graphics) or cs.DB (Databases). The use of Markov Random Field (MRF) and the proposed methodology for detecting non-annotated buildings involve machine learning techniques, which could place the paper in cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) or cs.LG (Machine Learning).
